<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Taking Belonging for Granite Research Poster</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Lora:ital,wght@0,400;0,500;1,400;1,500&family=Source+Sans+3:wght@300;400;500;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

  body {
    background: #D8D4CC;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: flex-start;
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 1rem;
    font-family: 'Source Sans 3', sans-serif;
  }

  /*
    36" wide × 24" tall = 3:2 landscape ratio
    Screen preview: 1200px wide × 800px tall
    Print: set browser to 36in × 24in custom paper size, 100% scale, no margins
  */
  .poster {
    width: 1200px;
    height: 800px;
    background: #F5F2EB;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-rows: 108px 1fr;
    overflow: hidden;
    position: relative;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .poster::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 90% 5%, rgba(90,110,58,0.05) 0%, transparent 55%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 5% 95%, rgba(90,110,58,0.04) 0%, transparent 55%);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 0;
  }

  .header {
    background: #2C3D1A;
    padding: 0 1.8rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    z-index: 1;
    position: relative;
  }

  .title {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 1.6rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #F0EDE4;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .title .pun {
    font-style: italic;
    color: #B5D180;
  }

  .byline {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: #9DB876;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .header-badge {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);
    border: 1px solid rgba(181,209,128,0.35);
    color: #B5D180;
    font-size: 0.63rem;
    padding: 0.35rem 0.8rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    white-space: nowrap;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    text-align: center;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* 4 columns × 2 rows landscape layout */
  .body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1.05fr 1.05fr 1.2fr 1fr;
    grid-template-rows: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    padding: 0.6rem;
    z-index: 1;
    position: relative;
  }

  .card {
    background: #FDFAF4;
    border: 0.5px solid #C8C2AC;
    border-radius: 7px;
    padding: 0.7rem 0.8rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .card.dark { background: #2C3D1A; border-color: #2C3D1A; }
  .card.mid  { background: #3B5220; border-color: #3B5220; }
  .card.tall { grid-row: span 2; }

  .card-label {
    font-size: 0.56rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: #5A6E3A;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .card.dark .card-label,
  .card.mid  .card-label { color: #9DB876; }

  .card-heading {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #2C3D1A;
    line-height: 1.25;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .card.dark .card-heading,
  .card.mid  .card-heading { color: #F0EDE4; }

  .card-body {
    font-size: 0.62rem;
    color: #4A4840;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }
  .card.dark .card-body,
  .card.mid  .card-body { color: #D0CCB8; }

  .stat-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .stat-item {
    background: #EAF0DC;
    border-radius: 5px;
    padding: 0.3rem 0.4rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .stat-num {
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: #2C3D1A;
    display: block;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.5rem;
    color: #5A6E3A;
    line-height: 1.35;
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.1rem;
  }

  .finding-box {
    background: #EAF0DC;
    border-left: 3px solid #5A6E3A;
    border-radius: 0 5px 5px 0;
    padding: 0.38rem 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    color: #2C3D1A;
    line-height: 1.45;
    font-style: italic;
    font-family: 'Lora', serif;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .finding-box.light {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
    border-left-color: #9DB876;
    color: #E0DCC8;
  }

  .finding-box + .finding-box { margin-top: 0.3rem; }

  .tag-row {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .tag { background: #E0DAC8; color: #3B3A2E; border-radius: 3px; padding: 0.1rem 0.38rem; font-size: 0.52rem; font-weight: 500; }
  .tag.green      { background: #C8D9A8; color: #27400F; }
  .tag.dark-green { background: rgba(157,184,118,0.18); color: #B5D180; }

  .rq-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.42rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .rq-num {
    background: #5A6E3A;
    color: #F0EDE4;
    border-radius: 50%;
    width: 1.1em;
    height: 1.1em;
    min-width: 1.1em;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 0.56rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 0.1em;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .rq-text { font-size: 0.61rem; color: #4A4840; line-height: 1.45; }

  .method-step {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.38rem;
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    color: #D0CCB8;
    padding: 0.2rem 0;
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07);
  }
  .method-step:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

  .method-dot {
    width: 5px;
    height: 5px;
    min-width: 5px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #9DB876;
  }

  .framework-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0.45rem 0.55rem;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .fw-author { font-size: 0.58rem; font-weight: 600; color: #5A6E3A; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 0.15rem; }
  .fw-desc   { font-size: 0.56rem; color: #4A4840; line-height: 1.45; }

  .divider { height: 0.5px; background: #C8C2AC; margin: 0.25rem 0; flex-shrink: 0; }

  @media print {
    body { background: white; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .poster { width: 36in; height: 24in; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="poster">

  <!-- HEADER -->
  <div class="header">
    <div>
      <div class="title">
        <span class="pun">Taking Belonging for Granite:</span> Identity Research in Science Education
      </div>
      <div class="byline">Natasha Lawson &nbsp;·&nbsp; Science Education Department &nbsp;·&nbsp; San José State University &nbsp;·&nbsp; 2025</div>
    </div>
    <div class="header-badge">Design-Based Research<br>2025–2026</div>
  </div>

  <!-- BODY: 4 columns × 2 rows, landscape -->
  <div class="body">

    <!-- COL 1 ROW 1: The Problem -->
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-label">The Problem</div>
      <div class="card-heading">Geoscience's Diversity Crisis</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        Geoscience is one of the least racially diverse fields in STEM. Underrepresented racial minority groups comprise just 7% of the field; a number unchanged over four decades. Hostile climates, the field's entanglement with colonial resource extraction, and structural barriers at every level continue to drive diverse scientists out before they can change the field from within.
      </div>
      <div class="stat-row" style="margin-top: auto;">
        <div class="stat-item">
          <span class="stat-num">7%</span>
          <span class="stat-label">underrepresented groups in geoscience (Wilson, 2017)</span>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-item">
          <span class="stat-num">50 yrs</span>
          <span class="stat-label">to gender parity at current rates (Bernard & Cooperdock, 2018)</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COL 2 ROW 1: The Gap -->
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-label">The Gap</div>
      <div class="card-heading">What We Don't Yet Know</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        Existing diversity initiatives focus on recruitment and retention but leave largely unexamined how geoscience PhD students understand and narrate their own intersecting identities. Without this knowledge, we cannot build the cultural conditions that make belonging sustainable rather than exceptional.
      </div>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div class="finding-box">
        Little is known about how PhD geoscientists construct their intersecting identities, or how asset-based frameworks might reshape that self-understanding over time.
      </div>
      <div class="finding-box" style="margin-top: 0.3rem;">
        This study fills that gap by examining how a year-long PD program shapes how graduate scientists see themselves.
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COL 3 ROWS 1+2: Preliminary Findings — tall -->
    <div class="card dark tall">
      <div class="card-label">Preliminary Findings</div>
      <div class="card-heading">A Surprising Identity Gap</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        Early observations reveal a striking and consistent tension in how geoscience PhD students narrate their own identities:
      </div>
      <div class="finding-box light">
        Participants do not identify as scientists despite years of active scientific training and research.
      </div>
      <div class="finding-box light">
        They believe they must be experts before they can educate others; creating a double barrier to both scientific and educator identities.
      </div>
      <div class="card-body" style="margin-top: 0.35rem;">
        The gap between what participants <em style="color: #B5D180;">do</em> every day and who they believe themselves to <em style="color: #B5D180;">be</em> suggests that diversifying geoscience requires more than changing who enters the field. It requires transforming how scientists understand themselves.
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
      Identity recognition not just representation is the lever for change.
      </div>
      <div class="tag-row" style="margin-top: auto;">
        <span class="tag dark-green">Science identity</span>
        <span class="tag dark-green">Educator identity</span>
        <span class="tag dark-green">Belonging</span>
        <span class="tag dark-green">Asset-based learning</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COL 4 ROW 1: Research Questions -->
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-label">Research Questions</div>
      <div class="card-heading">What This Study Asks</div>
      <div style="flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; margin-top: 0.2rem;">
        <div class="rq-item">
          <div class="rq-num">1</div>
          <div class="rq-text">How does a year-long professional development program modeling Culturally Sustaining Pedagogy shape geoscience PhD students' understanding of themselves as learners, educators, and scientists?</div>
        </div>
        <div class="rq-item">
          <div class="rq-num">2</div>
          <div class="rq-text">In what ways do asset-based frameworks inform geoscience PhD students' capacity to become advocates for equity and inclusion within their fields and communities?</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="font-size: 0.56rem; color: #5A6E3A; font-style: italic; font-family: 'Lora', serif;">
        8–10 PhD geoscience TAs · R1 university · Purposive sampling · Year-long
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COL 1 ROW 2: Theoretical Framework -->
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-label">Theoretical Framework</div>
      <div class="card-heading">Multiple Lenses on Identity</div>
      <div class="framework-grid" style="margin-top: 0.2rem;">
        <div>
          <div class="fw-author">Gee (2000)</div>
          <div class="fw-desc">Four overlapping identity types examined at individual and community levels</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="fw-author">Carlone & Johnson (2007)</div>
          <div class="fw-desc">Science identity: competence, recognition, and performance </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="fw-author">Paris & Alim (2017)</div>
          <div class="fw-desc">Culturally Sustaining Pedagogy (CSP): sustain cultural pluralism, not just bridge to dominant norms</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="fw-author">Moll et al. (1992)</div>
          <div class="fw-desc">Funds of Knowledge: rich cultural assets students carry that institutions routinely fail to recognize</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COL 2 ROW 2: Methodology -->
    <div class="card mid">
      <div class="card-label">Methodology</div>
      <div class="card-heading" style="color: #F0EDE4;">Design-Based Research using Narrative Analysis</div>
      <div style="flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; margin-top: 0.2rem;">
        <div class="method-step"><div class="method-dot"></div><span><b>Background questionnaires</b> baseline identity &amp; context</span></div>
        <div class="method-step"><div class="method-dot"></div><span><b>Pre-interviews</b> "Tell me about your journey as a science learner"</span></div>
        <div class="method-step"><div class="method-dot"></div><span><b>Monthly PD sessions</b> CSP modeled, recorded + field notes</span></div>
        <div class="method-step"><div class="method-dot"></div><span><b>Digital reflective handouts</b> ongoing identity documentation</span></div>
        <div class="method-step"><div class="method-dot"></div><span><b>Post-interviews </b> narrative change over time</span></div>
        <div class="method-step"><div class="method-dot"></div><span><b>Thematic analysis in Dedoose</b> intersectional frame (Crenshaw, 1989)</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="tag-row" style="margin-top: 0.3rem;">
        <span class="tag green">Purposive sampling</span>
        <span class="tag green">Qualitative</span>
        <span class="tag green">Year-long</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- COL 4 ROW 2: Significance -->
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-label">Why This Matters</div>
      <div class="card-heading">Significance for the Field</div>
      <div class="card-body">
        If PhD geoscientists cannot see themselves as scientists or educators, no amount of recruitment can build an inclusive field. Lasting change requires transforming the cultural conditions of graduate science education, starting with how scientists understand themselves.
      </div>
      <div class="finding-box" style="margin-top: auto;">
        "We will limit the science we do if we do not become more inclusive. We need to do better." — Bernard &amp; Cooperdock, 2018
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</div>
</body>
</html>
